00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:13,540
Kipnis: They're both human.
Schafer: They're human, yeah,
yeah, they're human.

330
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:23,166
Petty: Yeah, I think the idea's really cool and I think visually, I think there's a lot of interesting stuff that we have,

331
00:21:23,166 --> 00:21:27,000
I haven't really had a chance to talk to Tim yet, but I think there's a lot of interesting stuff thematically

332
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,840
that is appealing to me.

333
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:31,940
I mean, there's this sort of almost Tale of Two Cities quality to it.

334
00:21:31,940 --> 00:21:37,306
I can see a lot of good ambiguity in the way that that story is structured.

335
00:21:37,306 --> 00:21:39,300
I think that's really, will be great.

336
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:44,200
And to be a way that we, from a design and narrative way move the genre forward a little bit.

337
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:48,380
Kipnis: I want, I want something new to be brought to the table that wasn't there before.

338
00:21:49,620 --> 00:21:56,200
And I'm not sure what that is quite yet because I still don't have like a very clear idea of what the game's going to be like.

339
00:21:57,660 --> 00:22:00,494
But hopefully I can contribute to that.

